Day 02 – Users & Permissions

What I Did

* Created and managed users and groups
* Modified file ownership
* Set and analyzed file permissions

---

Key Concepts

* User accounts and groups
* File ownership
* Permission structure (read, write, execute)

---

Commands Used

See `commands.sh`

---

What I Learned

User and permission management is critical for securing a Linux system. Proper access control ensures that only authorized users can modify or execute files.

---

Why It Matters

Misconfigured permissions are one of the most common security issues. Understanding this allows a sysadmin to protect systems and enforce access policies.

